{
  "text": "Transthoracic echocardiography was performed with a Vivid 7 (GE, Vingmed Ultrasound, Horton, Norway) ultrasound system by experienced ultrasound technicians. Aortic root diameters were measured in end-diastole at the level of the sinus of Valsalva, by using the leading edge to leading edge technique in parasternal long axis, consistent with the current American Society of Echocardiography guidelines. [CITATION_1] Computed tomography was performed by the use of a Philips 64 slice CT scanner, using generally available iodine-based contrast agents in a small number of patients.",
